msgstr "Stabiele PPA (Bevat alleen officiële releases)"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../installation.rst:133
msgid "Daily PPA (Highly experimental and unstable, for testers)"
msgstr "Dagelijkse PPA (Zeer experimenteel en onstabiel, voor testers)"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../installation.rst:142
msgid "Chrome OS (Chromebook)"
msgstr "Chrome OS (Chromebook)"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../installation.rst:144
msgid ""
"Chrome OS supports Linux apps, but this feature is off by default. You can "
"turn it on in *Settings*. Once Linux is enabled, you can install and run "
"OpenShot Linux AppImages on any *x86-based* Chromebook. The command below "
"will download our AppImage and configure your system to run OpenShot "
"successfully."
msgstr ""
"Chrome OS ondersteunt Linux-apps, maar deze functie is standaard "
"uitgeschakeld. U kunt deze inschakelen in *Instellingen*. Zodra Linux is "
"ingeschakeld, kunt u OpenShot Linux AppImages installeren en uitvoeren op "
"elke *x86-gebaseerde* Chromebook. De onderstaande opdracht downloadt onze "
"AppImage en configureert uw systeem om OpenShot succesvol uit te voeren."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
